\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals or perennials. Leaves flat or convolute, narrow; ligule a ring of hairs (rarely membranous). Inflorescence a panicle. Spikelets laterally compressed, with 2-many florets. Glumes unequal to subequal, membranous, shorter than the florets, 1-veined. Lemma 3-veined, membranous, usually unawned, falling separately or with the palea and grain. Palea hyaline, 2-keeled often persistent. Stamens 3 or 2. Lodicules 2, minute, rarely absent, not toothed.
